        "intro_body": "Solar panels that only work in perfect sunlight. Power banks that die the second you actually need them. Gas generators loud enough to announce your location to anyone in a three-block radius.\n\nEvery company claims to have the magic fix for when the lights go out. Most of them haven't been within 10 miles of a real blackout.\n\nThat's why, as someone who's spent 14 years in emergency preparedness - from hurricane response to off-grid survival training - I decided to put the most talked-about portable power solutions to the test.\n\nTogether with my team, we ranked each one based on what actually matters during a real emergency: reliability when every other option has failed you.",
